# Commute Route Visualization — Location Analysis Overhaul

Redesign the `LocationAnalysis` section in the Role Viewport's Analysis tab to be a premium, map-centered commute visualization with live route data and AI-powered metrics charts.

## Context

The user wants the entire location analysis section to showcase the commute journey from **126 Colby St, San Francisco** (Point A) to **the employer's office** (Point B) using a zoomed-in interactive map with the actual driving route, plus AI-populated metric charts — all in one cohesive component. Credits to contributors are also requested.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **mapcn (MapLibre GL)** will be used as the map library. It's installed via `npx shadcn@latest add @mapcn/map` and provides `Map`, `MapRoute`, `MapMarker`, `MarkerContent`, `MarkerLabel`, `MapControls` — all composable React components styled with Tailwind that fit perfectly with the existing shadcn dark UI.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **OSRM** (Open Source Routing Machine — `router.project-osrm.org`) is used client-side for the route GeoJSON. This is a free, open, and publicly-available routing API that returns actual road geometry — no API key needed. The existing OpenRoute/Google Maps backend service provides the *metrics* (distance, duration) but not the geometry; OSRM fills that gap beautifully on the frontend.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **OpenRoute Service (HeiGIT)** will supply geocoding on the backend via the existing `OpenRouteService.geocode()` method. A new API endpoint (`GET /api/roles/:roleId/commute-route`) will return the start/end coordinates and precomputed metrics so the frontend can fetch the OSRM geometry and display the route.

