## Proposed Changes

### Backend — New Commute Route API Endpoint

Adds a lightweight API endpoint that returns geocoded start/end coordinates plus cached distance/duration so the frontend can render the map route without needing its own API keys.

#### [NEW] [commute-route.ts](file:///Volumes/Projects/workers/core-resumes/src/backend/api/routes/commute-route.ts)

New Hono route: `GET /api/roles/:roleId/commute-route`

Returns:
```json
{
  "start": { "name": "126 Colby St", "lng": -122.405, "lat": 37.711 },
  "end": { "name": "Company HQ, City", "lng": -122.0842, "lat": 37.4220 },
  "distanceMiles": 33.2,
  "durationMinutes": 38,
  "source": "openroute"
}
```

Logic:
1. Reads the role's metadata to determine `location` (same `caLocations` → `rawLocation` fallback used by `role-insights.ts`)
2. Uses `OpenRouteService.geocode()` to resolve both start/end coordinates
3. Uses `OpenRouteService.getCommuteSummary()` for distance/duration
4. Returns JSON with all data needed by the frontend

