### Frontend — New `CommuteRouteMap` Component

#### [NEW] [CommuteRouteMap.tsx](file:///Volumes/Projects/workers/core-resumes/src/frontend/components/role/CommuteRouteMap.tsx)

A full-width, premium commute visualization with:

1. **Interactive MapLibre map** — dark-themed tiles (Carto Dark Matter), zoomed and auto-bounded to fit the route
2. **OSRM driving route** — rendered as a glowing animated line from Point A to Point B
3. **Custom markers** — 🏠 at 126 Colby (green) and 🏢 at employer (blue) with labeled tooltips
4. **Floating metrics overlay** — glassmorphism cards positioned over the map showing:
   - Distance (miles)
   - Drive time (minutes)
   - Data source badge (OpenRoute / Google Maps)
5. **Credits footer** — Attribution to contributors: HeiGIT/OpenRouteService (routing data), OSRM (route geometry), Carto (map tiles), MapLibre GL (renderer), mapcn by Anmol Saini (component library), Google Maps API (fallback provider), and Antigravity (prior revisions of this analysis UI)

